      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. i've also heard some people say that the focus on nonviolence was actually kind of a way to co-opt more radical movements that wanted much faster or more aggressive change. would u say the \"official\" history mostly ignores the more militant groups because they don't fit the narrative of peaceful progress?",
